Kafka Concepts

Producer → Sends messages to Kafka topics.

Consumer → Reads messages from Kafka topics.

Broker → Kafka server that stores and serves messages.

Topic → Category/channel where messages are stored.

Partition → A topic division used for parallel processing.

Offset → Unique position of a message within a partition.

Consumer Group → Multiple consumers working together to consume messages.

Replication Factor → Number of copies of a partition stored across brokers.

Leader Partition → Handles all reads and writes for a partition.

Follower Partition → Replica that copies data from the leader.

Kafka Cluster → Group of Kafka brokers working together.

Serialization → Converting objects into bytes for transmission.

Deserialization → Converting bytes back into objects.

auto-offset-reset=earliest → Reads messages from the beginning if no offset exists.

auto-offset-reset=latest → Reads only new messages after the consumer starts.

